ent%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20India's%20Balakot%20strikes%2C%20several%20countries%20offered%20to%20send%20special%20envoys%20and%20China%20too%20suggested%20that%20it%20could%20send%20its%20deputy%20minister%20to%20both%20countries%20to%20seek%20de-escalation%20but%20New%20Delhi%20declined%20the%20offer%2C%20says%20former%20diplomat%20Ajay%20Bisaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20upcoming%20book%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%2C%20who%20was%20serving%20as%20Indian%20High%20Commissioner%20to%20Islamabad%20in%20that%20period%2C%20also%20writes%20that%20India%20was%20willing%20to%20send%20an%20aircraft%20of%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20to%20Pakistan%20to%20bring%20back%20Wing%20Commander%20Abhinandan%20Varthaman%2C%20but%20the%20Pakistani%20government%20refused%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVarthaman%20(now%20Group%20Captain)%20downed%20a%20Pakistani%20jet%20on%20February%2027%2C%202019%2C%20before%20his%20MiG%2021%20Bison%20jet%20was%20hit%20in%20a%20dogfight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20had%20launched%20the%20retaliation%20for%20the%20Balakot%20airstrikes%20a%20day%20before.%20Varthaman%20was%20captured%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20Army%20and%20was%20released%20two%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20willing%20to%20send%20an%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20aircraft%20to%20pick%20him%20up%20but%20Pakistan%20refused%20permission%3B%20the%20optics%20of%20an%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20plane%20landing%20in%20Islamabad%20after%20all%20that%20had%20happened%20over%20the%20previous%20three%20days%2C%20was%2C%20of%20course%2C%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Pakistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%2C%20'Anger%20Management%3A%20The%20Troubled%20Diplomatic%20Relationship%20Between%20India%20and%20Pakistan'%2C%20he%20also%20says%20several%20countries%20had%20offered%20to%20send%20special%20envoys%20over%20to%20the%20subcontinent%20but%20this%20was%20no%20longer%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20China%2C%20not%20to%20be%20left%20behind%2C%20had%20suggested%20that%20it%20could%20send%20its%20deputy%20minister%20to%20both%20countries%20to%20seek%20de-escalation.%20India%20had%20politely%20declined%20the%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%20published%20by%20Rupa%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%2C%20who%20had%20a%20distinguished%20diplomatic%20career%20spanning%2035%20years%2C%20delves%20into%20various%20aspects%20of%20India-Pakistan%20relations%20since%20Independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ties%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20came%20under%20severe%20strain%20after%20India's%20warplanes%20pounded%20a%20Jaish-e-Mohammed%20terrorist%20training%20camp%20in%20Balakot%20in%20Pakistan%20on%20February%2026%2C%202019%2C%20in%20response%20to%20the%20Pulwama%20terror%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20says%20that%20the%20day%20after%20India's%20air%20strikes%20at%20Balakot%2C%20the%20ambassadors%20of%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20and%20France%20were%20informed%20during%20a%20briefing%20by%20the%20then%20Pakistan%20foreign%20secretary%20Tehmina%20Janjua%20about%20a%20message%20she%20received%20from%20the%20Pakistan%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bnine%20missiles%20from%20India%20had%20been%20pointed%20towards%20Pakistan%2C%20to%20be%20launched%20any%20time%20that%20day%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20foreign%20secretary%20requested%20the%20envoys%20to%20report%20this%20intelligence%20to%20their%20capitals%20and%20ask%20India%20not%20to%20escalate%20the%20situation.%20The%20diplomats%20promptly%20reported%20these%20developments%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20flurry%20of%20diplomatic%20activity%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20P5%20capitals%2C%20and%20in%20New%20Delhi%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20permanent%20members%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%20and%20France%20are%20known%20as%20P5%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20them%20recommended%20to%20her%20that%20Pakistan%20should%20convey%20its%20concerns%20directly%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Bisaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20also%20writes%20that%20then%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20wanted%20to%20talk%20to%20his%20Indian%20counterpart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20around%20midnight%20I%20got%20a%20call%20in%20Delhi%20from%20Pakistani%20High%20Commissioner%20Sohail%20Mahmood%2C%20now%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20who%20said%20that%20PM%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20keen%20to%20talk%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20checked%20upstairs%20and%20responded%20that%20our%20prime%20minister%20was%20not%20available%20at%20this%20hour%20but%20in%20case%20Imran%20Khan%20had%20any%20urgent%20message%20to%20convey%20he%20could%2C%20of%20course%2C%20convey%20it%20to%20me.%20I%20got%20no%20call%20back%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20and%20UK%20envoys%20in%20Delhi%20got%20back%20overnight%20to%20India's%20foreign%20secretary%20to%20claim%20that%20Pakistan%20was%20now%20ready%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation%2C%20to%20act%20on%20India's%20dossier%2C%20and%20to%20seriously%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20says%20%26quot%3BPakistan's%20PM%20would%20himself%20make%20these%20announcements%20and%20the%20pilot%20would%20be%20returned%20to%20India%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20India's%20%26quot%3Bcoercive%20diplomacy%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20effective%2C%20its%20expectations%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20of%20the%20world%20had%20been%20clear%2C%20backed%20by%20a%20credible%20resolve%20to%20escalate%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20would%20later%20say%20in%20a%20campaign%20speech%20that%2C%20'Fortunately%2C%20Pakistan%20announced%20that%20the%20pilot%20would%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20India.%20Else%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20%3Cem%3Eqatal%20ki%20raat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20night%20of%20bloodshed'%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20overall%20regional%20geopolitics%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes%20that%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Imran%20Khan%20conveyed%20to%20China%20that%20it%20should%20support%20Islamabad%20since%20the%20United%20States%20decided%20to%20back%20India%20against%20China%2C%20but%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20%26quot%3Bdeclared%20that%20China%20would%20not%20be%20propping%20up%20Pakistan%20against%20India%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20also%20learnt%20that%20Khan%20had%20told%20the%20Chinese%20that%20they%20should%20support%20Pakistan%20since%20the%20US%20had%20decided%20to%20support%20India%20against%20China.%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20apparently%20responded%20sharply%20to%20Imran%20Khan%20for%20this%20simplistic%20geopolitical%20assessment%20and%20declared%20that%20China%20would%20not%20be%20propping%20up%20Pakistan%20against%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20had%20advised%20Khan%20that%20it%20was%20the%20US%20that%20could%20help%20Pakistan%20in%20its%20India%20relationship%20and%20it%20would%20be%20in%20Pakistan's%20interest%20to%20make%20up%20with%20the%20US%20as%20well%20as%20with%20Afghanistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704734220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2Fros2r47s_india-flag-generic_625x300_11_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-delhi-declined-chinas-offer-to-send-deputy-minister-to-india-pak-after-2019-balakot-strikes-4824661%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20India's%20Balakot%20strikes%2C%2