t%20on%20Sunday%20is%20said%20to%20have%20begun%20at%209%20pm%20and%20no%20casualties%20have%20been%20reported%20so%20far.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fanother-gunfight-reported-in-manipurs-moreh-locals-accuse-state-police-of-bias%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nehru-Patel%20Treated%20China%20as%20Equal%2C%20Modi%20Has%20Conceded%20a%20Power%20Differential%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28091355%2Fmodi-xi-bishek-pib.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20note%20written%20by%20Sardar%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20home%20minister%2C%20in%201949%20on%20the%20view%20India%20ought%20to%20take%20of%20China%20is%20once%20again%20in%20the%20news.%20It%20is%20fairly%20well%20known%20that%20Sardar%20Patel%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20had%20adopted%20a%20different%20approach%20on%20some%20issues%2C%20but%20that%20Patel%20deferred%20to%20Nehru%20on%20such%20matters.%20Four%20points%20need%20to%20be%20remembered%20while%20analysing%20the%20difference%20in%20the%20approach%20of%20the%20two%20great%20leaders.%20First%2C%20that%20Patel%20felt%20free%20enough%20to%20pen%20down%20his%20views%2C%20differing%20with%20those%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20recorded%20them%20for%20posterity.%20He%20was%20not%20intimidated%20by%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20wider%20and%20deeper%20knowledge%20of%20world%20affairs%20and%20world%20history%2C%20a%20fact%20that%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20himself%20had%20recognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20both%20leaders%20were%20dealing%20with%20a%20decolonising%20Asia%20in%20rapid%20transition.%20Both%20China%20and%20India%20and%2C%20indeed%2C%20much%20of%20Asia%20had%20entered%20a%20new%20world%20as%20new%20entities%20with%20new%20leaderships.%20In%20today%E2%80%99s%20more%20settled%20world%2C%20despite%20all%20the%20uncertainties%20that%20characterise%20the%20post-Cold%20War%20world%2C%20it%20is%20not%20often%20easy%20for%20younger%20generations%20to%20comprehend%20the%20uncertainties%20of%20that%20new%20post-colonial%2C%20post-war%20era.%20Everyone%20was%20experimenting.%20Everyone%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccrossing%20the%20river%20by%20touching%20the%20stones%E2%80%9D%2C%20to%20quote%20a%20famous%20Chinese%20folk%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20dominant%20sentiment%20in%20India%20at%20the%20time%20in%20thinking%20about%20the%20world%20was%20the%20anti-colonial%20sentiment.%20Differences%20may%20have%20been%20there%20in%20the%20way%20Pandit%20Nehru%20and%20Sardar%20Patel%20viewed%20the%20world%20and%20in%20the%20way%20that%20other%20nascent%20political%20groups%20did%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20everyone%20was%20united%20by%20a%20patriotism%20born%20in%20the%20crucible%20of%20the%20anti-colonial%20freedom%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20post-colonial%20leaderships%20of%20both%20China%20and%20India%20were%20still%20very%20nervous%20about%20their%20hold%20over%20their%20newly-constituted%20nations%20and%20territories.%20It%20would%20be%20no%20exaggeration%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20Communist%20leadership%20in%20China%20was%20perhaps%20as%20nervous%20about%20its%20hold%20over%20its%20far-%20flung%20borders%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20was.%20If%20Mao%20Zedong%20wanted%20to%20secure%20control%20over%20Tibet%2C%20Nehru%20and%20Patel%20too%20would%20have%20wanted%20to%20secure%20control%20over%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20North-East%20Frontier%20Agency%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20succeeded%20in%20full%20measure%2C%20but%20very%20quickly%20came%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Cground%20realities%E2%80%9D.%20To%20judge%20them%20today%20based%20on%20the%20perceptions%20gained%20over%20time%2C%20through%20lenses%20acquired%2C%20dispensed%20with%20and%20re-acquired%20over%20time%2C%20does%20not%20do%20justice%20to%20their%20intellectual%20acumen%20nor%20to%20their%20nationalism%20and%20commitment%20to%20building%20a%20truly%20%E2%80%9CNew%20India%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20an%20independent%2C%20new%20republic%20of%20many%20%E2%80%9Cnationalities%E2%80%9D%2C%20ethnicities%2C%20linguistic%20groups%20and%20religious%20faiths.%20It%20is%20easy%20for%20many%20today%20to%20assert%20that%20India%20is%20in%20fact%20%E2%80%9CBharat%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20the%20present%20is%20but%20a%20natural%20inheritor%20of%20a%20distant%20past.%20However%2C%20in%20the%201940s%20and%201950s%20the%20republic%20was%20still%20being%20constituted%20as%20one%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20process%2C%20many%20newly%20independent%20nations%20made%20many%20mistakes.%20Some%20like%20Korea%20and%20Vietnam%20came%20into%20being%20as%20free%20nations%20and%20were%20immediately%20split%20up.%20Others%20like%20India%20were%20first%20split%20up%20before%20being%20created.%20Many%20others%20were%20first%20imagined%20on%20paper%20and%20then%20constituted%20into%20nations%20on%20the%20ground.%20One%20must%20enter%20the%20mind%20of%20the%20political%20leadership%20of%20those%20times%20to%20understand%20their%20fears%20and%20aspirations.%20To%20adopt%20a%20superior%20attitude%20today%20in%20faulting%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20past%20would%20be%20churlish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%20that%20despite%20the%201962%20war%2C%20and%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20the%20leaderships%20of%20both%20China%20and%20India%20have%20sought%20to%20maintain%20stability%20in%20their%20relationship.%20What%20%E2%80%9Cdestabilised%E2%80%9D%20the%20relationship%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20was%20the%20sharply%20differential%20performance%20of%20both%20their%20economies%20between%201990%20and%202010.%20China%E2%80%99s%20emergence%20as%20the%20second%20biggest%20economy%20and%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trading%20power%20placed%20it%20in%20a%20category%20of%20its%20own.%20By%202010%2C%20China%20began%20viewing%20itself%20as%20a%20global%20power%20in%20the%20same%20league%20as%20the%20United%20States.%20India%2C%20it%20believed%2C%20was%20still%20a%20developing%20economy%20in%20the%20company%20of%20many%20other%20Asian%20and%20African%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20in%20a%20recent%20comment%20on%20the%20bilateral%20relationship%20by%20China%E2%80%99s%20English-language%20publication%2C%20Global%20Times%2C%20a%20Chinese%20commentator%20has%20noted%20that%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20was%20now%20adopting%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20view%20of%20where%20China%20and%20India%20stood.%20By%20not%20allowing%20the%20border%20issue%2C%20with%20China%20occupying%20newly%20acquired%20territory%20along%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%9CLine%20of%20Actual%20Control%E2%80%9D%20to%20further%20mar%20the%20relationship%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20yielded%20space%20and%20conceded%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEqually%20importantly%2C%20by%20repeatedly%20drawing%20attention%20to%20the%20difference%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20two%20economies%20and%20urging%20Indians%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20this%20reality%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20changed%20the%20debate%20around%20the%20trade%20deficit.%20In%20a%20tongue-in-cheek%20remark%2C%20Zhang%20Jiadong%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20South%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20Fudan%20University%2C%20draws%20attention%20to%20a%20change%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20the%20huge%20trade%20deficit%20that%20it%20faces%20in%20its%20bilateral%20trade%20with%20China.%20Says%20Mr%20Zhang%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20discussing%20the%20trade%20imbalance%20between%20China%20and%20India%2C%20Indian%20representatives%20earlier%20used%20to%20primarily%20focus%20on%20China%E2%80%99s%20measures%20to%20reduce%20the%20trade%20imbalance.%20But%20now%20they%20are%20placing%20more%20emphasis%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20export%20potential.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20what%20Mr%20Zhang%20is%20saying%20is%20that%20rather%20than%20complain%20about%20China%E2%80%99s%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunlevel%E2%80%9D%20trade%20playing%20field%2C%20as%20India%20did%20for%20close%20to%20two%20decades%2C%20including%20through%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20first%20term%2C%20it%20had%20now%20come%20around%20to%20accept%20the%20size%20differential%20between%20the%20two%20and%20it%20now%20views%20the%20trade%20deficit%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Climited%E2%80%9D%20export%20potential%20and%20weak%20performance.%20This%20is%20a%20neat%20swipe%2C%20and%20so%20far%2C%20we%20have%20not%20heard%20any%20protestations%20from%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20spokespersons%20or%20the%20Swadeshi%20Jagran%20Manch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20remark%20on%20the%20approach%20to%20the%20trade%20imbalance%20lies%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Chinese%20view%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20status.%20China%20merely%20wants%20India%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20power%20differential%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpotential%E2%80%9D.%20Interestingly%2C%20Mr%20Zhang%20seems%20to%20suggest%20that%20Narendra%20Modi%20may%20have%20finally%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20it.%20Both%20Patel%20and%20Nehru%20believed%20that%20China%20and%20India%20were%20equals%2C%20while%20neither%20Mao%20Zedong%20nor%20Zhou%20Enlai%20did%20so.%20Patel%20and%20Nehru%20adopted%20different%20perspectives%20on%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20imbalance%2C%20in%20perceptions%20and%20performance%2C%20as%20have%20subsequent%20Indian%20leaders.%20This%20debate%20will%20go%20on%20till%20India%20ups%20its%20performance.%20Posturing%20will%20not%20do%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjaya%20Baru%20is%20an%20economist%2C%20a%20former%20newspaper%20editor%2C%20a%20best-selling%20author%2C%20and%20former%20adviser%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fopinion%2Fcolumnists%2F070124%2Fsanjaya-baru-india-china-of-power-performance-posturing.html%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20Deccan%20Chronicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704697214000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28091355%2Fmodi-xi-bishek-pib.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnehru-patel-treated-china-as-equal-modi-has-conceded-a-power-differential%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22y%20not%20allowing%20the%20border%20issue%2C%20with%20China%20occupying%20newly%20acquired%20territory%20along%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3BLine%20of%20Actual%20Control%26quot%3B%20to%20further%20mar%20the%20relationship%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20yielded%20space%20and%20conceded%20ground.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnehru-patel-treated-china-as-equal-modi-has-conceded-a-power-differential%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%20three%20dead%20as%20Russia%20launches%20'large-scale%20missile%20attacks'%20on%20'peaceful%20cities'%20across%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704697080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-ukraine-kryvyi-millise_6414702.jpg%3F20240108094436%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fat-least-three-dead-as-russia-launches-large-scale-missile-attacks-on-peaceful-cities-across-ukraine-13043906%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20has%20launched%20a%20large-scale%20missile%20attack%20across%20Ukraine%2C%20with%20at%20least%20three%20people%20dead%20after%20residential%20and%20industrial%20buildings%20were%20hit%2C%20Ukrainian%20authorities%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A242%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fat-least-three-dead-as-russia-launches-large-scale-missile-attacks-on-peaceful