22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F05161643%2F25864047814_2d77293f02_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Southern%20states%20should%20get%20a%20%E2%80%9Cslightly%20larger%20portion%E2%80%9D%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20through%20a%20%E2%80%9Crecorrection%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20fiscal%20range%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%E2%80%9D%20from%20growing%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20political%20representation%20of%20these%20states%20change%20post%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20in%202026%2C%20former%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%20(CEA)%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20said%20on%20Sunday%20(January%207).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fsouthern-states-should-get-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian-2839000%5C%22%3Equoted%20him%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20wedge%20between%20fiscal%20power%20and%20contribution%20and%20political%20power%20is%20going%20to%20rise.%20However%2C%20he%20expressed%20hope%20that%20the%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20will%20address%20these%20critical%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20political%20representation%20is%20changed%2C%20which%20gives%20more%20relative%20power%20to%20the%20Hindi%20Heartland%20relative%20to%20the%20Southern%20states%20that%20have%20slower%20population%20growth%2C%20the%20disaffection%20will%20grow%20because%20the%20Southern%20states%20will%20say%20we%20contribute%20much%20more%20fiscally%20(but)%20we%20are%20losing%20political%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20Subramanian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouthern%20states%2C%20including%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20should%20retain%20a%20slightly%20larger%20portion%20of%20resources%20that%20are%20coming%20from%20the%20Centre.%20I%20think%20that%20has%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20new%20social%20contract%20going%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20CEA%20made%20these%20comments%20at%20an%20interactive%20session%2C%20in%20which%20another%20former%20CEA%20and%20former%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20governor%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20were%20also%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajan%2C%20who%20is%20also%20advising%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20like%20Subramanian%2C%20said%20India%20is%20too%20big%20to%20be%20run%20only%20from%20New%20Delhi.%20He%20called%20for%20more%20finances%20to%20the%20states%20which%20are%20investing%20in%20huge%20infrastructure%20and%20social%20projects.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20issue%20between%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20states%20was%20that%20the%20former%20is%20raising%20a%20lot%20through%20cess%20which%20is%20not%20being%20shared%20with%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20the%20problem.%20I%20think%20the%2014th%20Finance%20commission%20tried%20to%20devolve%20more%20to%20the%20states%2C%20but%20we%20have%20got%20more%20towards%20the%20Centre%20slightly%20in%20the%2015th%20Finance%20commission%E2%80%A6States%20are%20extremely%20important%20and%20we%20need%20to%20devolve%20more%20finances%20to%20the%20states%20and%20(ensure)%20a%20steady%20devolution%20of%20funds%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rajan%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20and%20Rajan%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20come%20amid%20concerns%20among%20southern%20states%20that%20their%20allocation%20from%20the%20Centre%20has%20diminished%20over%20the%20years.%20They%20perceive%20a%20potential%20consequence%20for%20managing%20population%20growth%2C%20expressing%20concerns%20about%20a%20potential%20decrease%20in%20the%20number%20of%20parliamentary%20seats%20following%20the%202026%20delimitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20China%2B1%20strategy%2C%20Rajan%20said%20that%20India%20was%20attracting%20much%20less%20investments%20than%20it%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20as%20a%20lot%20of%20investments%20are%20going%20to%20countries%20like%20Vietnam%20and%20Mexico%2C%20which%20according%20to%20him%2C%20were%20scoring%20because%20of%20more%20regional%20trade%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20as%20a%20country%2C%20needs%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20this.%20How%20do%20we%20get%20more%20of%20that%20kind%20of%20flow%20which%20would%20mean%20negotiating%20more%20of%20these%20regional%20trade%20agreements%20from%20which%20of%20course%20states%20like%20Tamil%20Nadu%20will%20benefit%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20was%20losing%20out%20despite%20its%20advantages%20like%20huge%20manpower%20and%20domestic%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20and%20Rajan%20further%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20should%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20debt%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20power%20sector%2C%20which%20is%20one-third%20of%20the%20total%20debt%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20They%20also%20lauded%20the%20state%20government%20for%20initiating%20reforms%20in%20several%20sectors%20like%20increasing%20the%20property%20taxes%20and%20indexing%20them%20with%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704695444000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F05161643%2F25864047814_2d77293f02_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsouthern-states-should-retain-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20former%20CEA's%20remarks%20come%20amid%20concerns%20among%20southern%20states%20that%20their%20allocation%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20diminished%20over%20the%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsouthern-states-should-retain-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20May%20Have%20Missed%20Its%20Passenger%20Vehicle%20Fuel%20Efficiency%20Targets%20for%20FY23%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08114807%2F6471842381_250a77b183_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20missed%20its%20fuel%20efficiency%20target%20for%20passengers%20vehicles%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202023%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20initiative%2C%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20that%20India%20has%20failed%20to%20achieve%20this%20target%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Fauto-news%2Fpassenger-vehicle-makers-miss-fuel-efficiency-targets%2Farticleshow%2F106617808.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quoting%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20makers%20of%C2%A0passengers%20vehicles%20comprising%20cars%2C%20vans%2C%20and%20utility%20vehicles%20achieved%20corporate%20average%20fuel%20economy%20(CAF%C3%89)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20measure%20of%20carbon%20emission%20of%20a%20vehicle%20%E2%80%93%20of%20116.078%20gm%20per%20km%20in%20the%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20such%20vehicles%20have%20crossed%20the%20CO2%20threshold%20of%20113%20gm%20per%20km%20set%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20%26amp%3B%20Highways.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fauto%2Findian-carmakers-may-have-to-pay-up-to-370-crore-for-violating-emissions-norms-18296411.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNBC%20TV18%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20reported%20that%20the%20target%20applies%20for%20the%20industry-average%20kerb%20weight%20of%201145%20kg%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%20reports%20had%20said%20that%20carmakers%20could%20face%20penalties%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%20370%20crore%20for%20violating%20emission%20rules%20according%20to%20the%20upgraded%20Corporate%20Average%20Fuel%20Efficiency%20II%20or%20CAFE%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Energy%20Conservation%20law%20mandates%20carmakers%20to%20pay%20Rs%2025%2C000%20per%20unit%20if%20their%20fleet%20CO2%20emissions%20exceed%20the%20intended%20CAFE%20score%20by%200-4.7%20grams%20per%20kilometre%2C%20and%20Rs%2050%2C000%20per%20unit%20if%20they%20exceed%20by%20more%20than%204.7%20grams%20per%20kilometre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20still%20work-in-progress%2C%20and%20we%20have%20yet%20to%20take%20a%20final%20call%E2%80%A6The%20industry%20has%20managed%20to%20bring%20up%20the%20score%20from%20130%20gm%2Fkm%20to%20115-116%20now%20which%20is%20a%20great%20progress%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20insider%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20report%20noted%20that%20the%20public%20disclosure%20of%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20CAFE%20score%20has%20been%20delayed%20for%20more%20than%20two%20to%20three%20months.%20The%20official%20scores%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20published%20in%20the%20next%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704694745000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08114807%2F6471842381_250a77b183_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findia-may-have-missed-its-passenger-vehicle-fuel-efficiency-targets-for-fy23%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20public%20disclosure%20of%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20corporate%20average%20fuel%20economy%20or%20CAFE%20score%20has%20been%20delayed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findia-may-have-missed-its-passenger-vehicle-fuel-efficiency-targets-for-fy23%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Teacher%20finds%20missing%20part%20of%20plane%20that%20had%20mid-air%20blowout%20in%20his%20garden%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704690540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm